  "texts": [
    "Because of their size (often billions of parameters), these systems are sometimes called large language models (LLMs).",
    "Contemporary LLMs are artificial neural networks, which learn to map some input representation to an output by iteratively tuning the weights between neurons in different layers of the network.",
    "This tuning process is achieved by extensive training.",
    "Specifically, LLMs are trained using a token prediction paradigm: given a string of tokens (e.g., \"The cat sat on the ___\"), an LLM must predict which word is most likely to come next.",
    "4 By observing many sentences like this one, an LLM eventually tunes its weights to produce more accurate probability distributions over the upcoming token (e.g., \"mat\")."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}